<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Penstemon</i> <i>heterodoxus</i> is characteristically present and usually co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Achillea</i> <i>millefolium</i>, <i>Antennaria</i> <i>media</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>filifolia</i>, <i>Carex</i> <i>microptera</i>, <i>Cistanthe</i> <i>umbellata</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>parryi</i>, <i>Polygonum</i> <i>douglasii</i>, <i>Potentilla</i> <i>diversifolia</i> and <i>Senecio</i> <i>scorzonella</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 70 cm; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Subalpine mesic to xeric meadows and scree. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Penstemon heterodoxus</i> as a FACU plant. </div>
</div>

		
